description: Superman and Batman's first run-in with The Prankster and Mr. Freeze has ended in near disaster. The authorities close in on the Dark Knight as he races against time to save Clark's life. This looks like a job for...the Batmobile!
name: Detective Part 8

description: A third massive FLASH HC from superstar writer GEOFF JOHNS! THE FASTEST MAN ALIVE clashes with his Rogues Gallery, including CAPTAIN COLD, THE PIED PIPER, TRICKSTER and MIRROR MASTER! Collects THE FLASH #201-225 and WONDER WOMAN #214!
name: Vol. 3

volume.name: The Flash Omnibus by Geoff Johns

description:
Ant-Man lives again - but his daughter Stature has fallen in battle! The Scarlet Witch faces the judgement of the X-Men, and the Young Avengers must make a huge decision in the amazing conclusion of The Children's Crusade

Also: Luke Cage and Ms Marvel clash with Doctor Doom!

Includes material reprinted from Avengers: Childrens Crusade #9 and New Avengers #8-9.

The New Avengers clash with Superia and the forces of HAMMER and Mockingbird is the first to fall in battle!

Also: in 1959, Nick Fury and his team of Avengers invade the castle of the Red Skull!

Includes material reprinted from New Avengers #10-12.

Who is really controlling the Heroes for Hire? Misty Knight thinks its her, but the Puppet Master is lurking in the shadows!

Also: the Avengers Academy students go looking for revenge and the Hood is their target! Tigra gets some shocking news about her baby, and Giant-Man returns!

Includes material reprinted from Heroes for Hire #4 and Avengers Academy #7-8.
name: The Return Of Giant-Man!

description:
"The Ghost of Jean DeWolff" Anti-Venom returns to help Spider-Man wage war against Mister Negative and his criminal empire... whether Spidey wants him to or not. And when an all-new Wraith enters the fray, will she prove to be a friend or foe?

Also, if Anti-Venom wants to get his hands on Mister Negative, he'll have to get past Hammerhead and The Spot first! Of all the days for Aunt May to return to the F.E.A.S.T. Centre...

Plus, a mysterious super villain has weaponized Antarctic Vibranium to sell to dictators, madmen and terrorists across the globe! To stop this WMD, the US military unleashes the enhanced black ops agent Venom! First stop on his hunt: The Savage Land! But whos hunting whom? Venom soon discovers that death stalks these jungles in the deadly form of Kraven the Hunter! Dont miss your ringside seat to the grittiest, down-and-dirtiest brawl of the year! Venom vs. Kraven the Hunter!

Includes material reprinted from Amazing Spider-Man #662-663 and Venom #2

The Spider-Man story of the decade begins! New York has been Infested and the web grows as it gets ready to explode into Spider-Island! Normal people are getting Spider-Powers! But not all of them realise that with great power must also come... you know the rest. Okay, sure we often say Peter Parker's life will never be the same. But listen, pal, we've never been more serious. Heroes and villains are crawling all over Manhattan and no one knows why!

Plus, the long awaited grudge match between Venom and Spider-Man is here! Big action! Big intrigue! All presented in the mighty Marvel fashion!

Includes material reprinted from Amazing Spider-Man #666-667 and Venom #4.

Spider-Island continues! Spider-powered New York citizens! Spider-powered criminals! And Peter Parker fighting alongside Manhattan biggest superheroes as Peter Parker?!!

Also, the Hobgoblin decides its time to remove his rival Randy Robertson Permanently!

Plus, can the new Venom and Peter Parker put aside their differences to help save a man from himself?

Includes material reprinted from Amazing Spider-Man #668, Spider-Island: Deadly Foes, and Venom #5

Flash Thompson is dropped into Ground Zero of the Infestation but will he lose control of his emotions (and the Venom Symbiote) when his own father lies dying in the hospital?

Also, how can the heroes of NYC hope to contain millions of spider-powered New Yorkers? Also, is that a Six-armed Shocker?! All this plus: one of Spider-Islands biggest mysteries revealed!

Plus, classic action, as Spidey teams-up with the Punisher to wage war on new Yorks drug dealers!

Includes material reprinted from Venom #6, Amazing Spider-Man #669 and Amazing Spider-Man #330!

Spider-Island continues! Introducing J Jonah Jameson: the Spectacular Spider-Mayor!?! Plus, Spider-Man battles the Spider-King!

Also, Project Rebirth has been infested and Venoms going under deep cover to start exterminating some bugs starting with Anti-Venom!

Plus, classic action, as Spidey teams-up with the Punisher to wage war on New Yorks drug dealers!

Includes material reprinted from Amazing Spider-Man #670, Venom #7, and Amazing Spider-Man #330

Jubilee faces a life of eternal horror as she struggles to cope with the fallout of Curse of the Mutants! Can Wolverine save her, or is the only mercy he can offer a swift death...? A new story begins by Kathryn Immonen and Phil Noto.

Also: Deadpool accepts the biggest challenge of his career - he has to kill a planet! More craziness from Daniel Way and Carlo Barberi.

Includes material reprinted from Wolverine and Jubilee #1-2 and Deadpool #34.

Wolverine and Jubilee face a dragon in a cosmic void, courtesy of a very cunning vampire lady! Can Jubes be saved?

Also: Deadpool battles Id, the Living Moon but a lovestruck rival may screw up his brilliant plan!

Includes material reprinted from Wolverine and Jubilee #3-4 and Deadpool #35

X-Force has a new adversary: the psychic monster known as the Shadow King!

Also: Magneto discovers X-Forces existence, and the price of his silence is a dark mission for Wolverine!

Plus: Deadpool returns to Earth to face a not-so-friendly welcome home party from his closest friends who are now his worst enemies!

Includes material reprinted from Uncanny X-Force #8-9 and Deadpool #36.

A complete adventure! Agent Brand and the Beast have a really big problem the Brood are back! Shadowcat, Colossus and Storm get some outer space action as they battle the deadliest aliens alive!

Includes material reprinted from Astonishing X-Men #38, 40 and 42.

A new story begins! The Hulk has been badly injured in his fight with Zeus, and needs rest but hes out of luck! The Savage Land is calling, and an old enemy is out for revenge! Guest-starring Ka-Zar!

By Greg Pak and Dale Eaglesham.

Also: an old friend of Thunderbolt Ross appears and he wants the Red Hulk dead!

By Jeff Parker and Gabriel Hardman

Includes material reprinted from Inc Hulks #623-624 and Hulk #30.1.

The Hulk battles Miek with the fate of the Savage Land at stake but even if he wins, he may lose his son Skaar!

By Greg Pak and Dean Eaglesham.

Also: The Hulk, Red She-Hulk and Amadeus Cho encounter a very old enemy in Rome!

By Greg Pak and Tom Grummett.

Plus: The Red Hulk is on the run from General Fortean, but a new threat has been created: Zero/One!

By Jeff Parker, Tim Seeley and Gabriel Hardman.

Includes material reprinted from Incredible Hulks #625-626 and Hulk #31.

The traitor has been revealed, and #686 finally has the smoking gun necessary to bring him down once and for all. Only one problem though---central command has been infiltrated by zombie robots, and they're promising to execute a 'flesh sack' every ten minutes until their demands are met. And cut off from the rest of his team, Commander Sven has no choice but to form an alliance with the same man he's sworn to expose at all costs. Finally face-to-face with his enemy, yet on the run from ones even more dangerous, what Sven does next changes everything. 'Fearless Leader' goes penultimate, and this is where the future becomes set in stone...
name: Fearless Leader 5: The Cost

description: Secrets and desires cast long shadows in the third volume of Abouet and Oubrerie's highly regarded series about life in the Ivory Coast of the 1970s. It's a world of shifting values, where issues like arranged marriage and gay love have Aya and her friends yearning to break out of the confines of their community, while the ties of friendship and support draw them back into its familiarity. Distinctly African and brilliantly universal, the series offers an unflinching take on human strengths, foibles, and the capriciousness of our natures.
name: HC

description: Saint Germaine...is the man who cannot die and an award-winning series that spins tales of myth and history. "Ghost Dance", a self contained story featuring Saint Germaine and the mysterious Tarot reader who describes firsthand, the Sioux Indians' Ghost Dance which led to the final episode of the American Indian and essentially ended the Indian Wars.
Housley shares his suspicions with Matt's brother, and the corpses keep coming.

Collects the Finieous Fingers' stories originally published in Dragon Magazine issues 3, 4, 6, 7, 9-22, 25-28, 30, 33 and 35, alongside new story Finieous vs. The Cloud Giants, a Who's Who of the characters, and a biography of creator J.D. Webster.

description:
After establishing the world of the prickly heroine with the first two episodes of this classic series (combined in Fantagraphics The Extraordinary Adventures of Adle Blanc-Sec Volume 1), Jacques Tardi plunges us back into Belle-poque Paris for another double dosage of heroic derring-do, evil and crazy malefactors, mad actresses (yes, "Clara Benhardt" makes a return appearance) and monsters!

In The Mad Scientist the science that brought us revived dinosaurs now results in a pithecanthrope stalking the streets of the City of Light, climaxing in an amazing car chase involving a foe from the previous volume. Will the perpetually inept Inspector Caponi just make things worse? Probably. Then in the second episode, Mummies on Parade, the mummy glimpsed in Adles apartment in previous episodes comes alive! The volume concludes with the sudden startling (and delightful) incursion of some characters familiar to Tardi fans, and a shocking climax that leaves the future of both Adle and this series in doubt as World War I erupts. (Its the only story in the entire series not to feature an in our next episode teaser.)

The Extraordinary Adventure of Adle Blanc-Sec Volume 2 is the lucky seventh book in Fantagraphics acclaimed series of Tardi reprints, showcasing the rich variety of graphic novels from one of Frances greatest living cartoonists.
name: The Mad Scientist and Mummies On Parade

description:
Picking up right where Kevin Smith's Green Hornet left off! The Black Hornet is history, but a new, even deadlier threat has grown right in the heart of Century City, and it may already be too late for The Green Hornet and Kato to stop it. How can Green Hornet scare a street gang out of business when the gang members themselves have no fear of anything - even death? Is the horrifying power behind their fearless ferocity truly supernatural? And just who is Saint Death?

Collects issues #11-15 in one volume, along with complete cover gallery.
name: Volume Three

description:
Red hand. One of the world's most proficient assassins-for-hire. He's killed presidents, CEOs, generals and housewives. He's killed just about everything that walks the earth on two feet. Before all that, he was Hayashi Kato's protege. Now, Redhand's sights are set dead center on Hayashi and his current pupils, the new Green Hornet and Kato.

One by one, Red Hand is picking off Century City's undercover heroes, working his way up to a final confrontation with the man Redhand blames for his own loss of humanity- the original Kato. The stakes have never been greater for Britt Reid and company.

Along with the epic "The Devil You Know" arc, this collection contains two stand-alone Green Hornet tales. As the relationship between the new Green Hornet and Kato becomes more complicated, Britt and Mulan find themselves confronting two more relics from the past: a mad German engineer-thief and one of Britt's former MMA sparring partners.

This collection features Issues 16-21 of the hit series by Phil Hester, Ande Parks, Igor Vitorino and Ronan Cliquet as well as a complete cover gallery by Phil Hester, Jonathan Lau and Brian Denham.
name: Volume Four

description: Set in an "insect noir" Manhattan of the early fifties, BugHouse is the tumultuous story of Tenor saxophonist, Jimmy Watts, as he leads his talented jazz band of "bugs" from the swing era into the uncharted maelstrom of Bop. Never before has the art of music felt more alive and real on the printed page. And never before has a more "human" portrait of drug addiction been depicted in comics.
name: GN

description: Berlin: City of Stonespresents the first part of Jason Lutes' captivating trilogy, set in the twilight years of Germany's Weimar Republic. Kurt Severing, a journalist, and Marthe Muller, an art student, are the central figures in a broad cast of characters intertwined with the historical events unfolding around them. City of Stones covers eight months in Berlin, from September 1928 to May Day, 1929, meticulously documenting the hopes and struggles of its inhabitants as their future is darkened by the encroaching shadow of history.
name: Book One

description: Saint Germaine chronicles the life of one of Europe's most famous adventurers... the vagabond lover Casanova, who infected the high courts with his charm, wit, and persuasive manner. His claim to fame included his many affairs, his escape from a Venice prison that was deemed inescapable, his frequent ventures into spying, his service as a monk, and the fateful duel that finally catapulted him to the rank of "gentleman of the court". It is a story that you only thought you knew. A valuable friend of Saint Germaine, we witness the unfolding of one of history's most fascinating characters whose life was both tragic and uplifting. Saint Germaine is a being who claims immortality yet has died a thousand deaths. He has traversed the paths of mankind for untold years. He is the purveyor of light in a world slowly being consumed by shadows. He is Saint Germaine and death to him is nothing more than a state of consciousness.
Housley finds an ally and discovers that the psychiatrist is not all he seems. Saved From The Shredder text article by Michael Cherkas; the journey from script to finished page.
